  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The non-invasive estimation of left ventricular end diastolic pressure (LVeDP) is a main goal
      for performing an echocardiography in the routine clinical practice. Conflicting evidence
      exists about mitral E/e' ratio reliability for predicting high LVeDP
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
