  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age over 18 years

          -  Patient performing an echocardiography in the routine clinical practice

          -  Informed consent given

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Severe valve disease, valvular prostheses, calcification of the mitral valve, the
             history of myocardial infarction, atrial fibrillation, severe arrhythmias not allowing
             the Doppler analysis, pacemaker and any image by inadequate Doppler ultrasound

          -  Major person under legal protection (backup justice, trusteeship, guardianship),
             person deprived of liberty.
      </textblock>
